25|$|He was {{licensed}} by Coca-Cola International from 1990 to 1996 {{allowing him to}} use their images and bottle designs in his artwork, making him the first <b>Black</b> <b>American</b> {{licensed by}} the company to create paintings. He {{would go on to}} design paintings using <b>Black</b> <b>American</b> themes that would become Coca-Cola art collectibles in the form of serving trays, note cards, prints and other memorabilia. His first original Coca-Cola painting sold for $30,000, which at that time was the highest he had earned for a single painting. The value of his later works reached up to $1.5million.|$|E
